                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2427</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-09T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1916, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All the northern provinces including Chekiang have accepted succession of Li to
                    the presidency. As the southern provinces had before proclaimed him as the
                    rightful President he holds the reins of Government without opposition. It is,
                    however, expected that southern provinces will demand changes in the personnel
                    of Cabinet; there are many candidates to be considered and difficulties may not
                    be avoided in trying to satisfy all parties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
